title: Before 21 January 2021, will the Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA) enter into a consent order that would allow Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac to exit conservatorship?
preds: The time factor and changing of the guard at the white house ...
Barring something crazy, this appears it will be a decision left up to the Biden admin.

Secretary Munuchin has signaled he is unlikely to support a consent order in the waning days of the administration. Although Fannie and Freddie's regulator is supportive of the move and pushing for it to happen before JAN 21, he cannot do so without Munichin's approval. It appears the Treasury Sec is happy to let the Biden administration make the decision on the consent order.
Mnuchin has expressed his hesitation to push this through before inauguration, limited days to accomplish this, esp. with need to raise capital.
If the focus is on capital retention - there will be no consent order modification w/o further action - that is my view.
Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin will not be able to accomplish this before the end of the Trump administration.

The conservatorship arrangement is too big a pot of cash for the Democrats to give up. Right now, any profits from those entities is forwarded to the Treasury. Also, there are too many upper-echelon members of the Democrat Party that benefit from their continued relationship with those two entities. This will make it darn near impossible to allow those entities to return to their pre-2008 status.
To much unrest today for a major change in policy
Tough to do this without resolution of the SCOTUS case (not until June).
With only a few weeks of his term remaining, there are few days left to get a consent order signed
They will be to busy to take care of that unless there will be more public/financial pressure demanding their exit.
An easy win for a President looking for ‘last day’ easy wins.
